.TH "register_trigger" 9 "register_trigger" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
register_trigger \- Generic event_command @reg implementation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" register_trigger
.BI "(char *glob "  ","
.BI "struct event_trigger_ops *ops "  ","
.BI "struct event_trigger_data *data "  ","
.BI "struct trace_event_file *file "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "glob" 12
The raw string used to register the trigger
.IP "ops" 12
The trigger ops associated with the trigger
.IP "data" 12
Trigger-specific data to associate with the trigger
.IP "file" 12
The trace_event_file associated with the event
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Common implementation for event trigger registration.

Usually used directly as the \fIreg\fP method in event command
implementations.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, errno otherwise
